    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>3 Highbury Grove</placeName>
                    <date>16 January 1855</date>
                    <salute>My Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>The mistake is one of my making &amp; I will make it right when the vol for 1854 is sent by enclosing also that for 1853[.] You will then be precisely in the position I stated to you &amp; I must settle the matter with the late answer. I will leave the Glasses for you this afternoon &amp; I think you will be pleased with your bargain which is better by nearly three dozen good Glasses than I stated in my former note as I neglected to count one parcel of them</p>
                  <p>Most truly yours | J. S. Bowerbank</p>
                  <p>P.S. I regret having given you so much useless trouble about the Books</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
